###############################################
		Installing K8s
###############################################


Minikube --->   Google Container Engine ----> AWS ---> Manual Install

1. Minikube (Local Environment)
 	- Install kubectl client from 
 	https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl/
 	-  Download and install minicube installer from 
 	https://github.com/kubernetes/minikube/releases
 	
 	-Check the version of minikube 
 	 $minikube version
 	 
 	- Start the vm using vertual box:
 	$minikube start 
 	
 	- check the nodes:
 	 $kubectl get nodes
 	 
 	 
 	- See the dashboard:
 	 $ minikube dashboard
 	 
 	 
 	 
 	 
 2 Installation of K8s in Google cloud
 3. Installation of K8s in AWS Cloud:
 	1. Prequesties : Kubectl, kops, cli, domain, IAM access
 	3. Create bucket 
 	4. Create Clusters:
 		kops create clusters \
 		--cloud=aws \
 		--znoes=
 		-- dns=
 		--name=
 		--yes
 		
 4. Installation manually with kubeadm
 	
 	